Preheat the oven to 200°C. Put a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{0.5%tsp} on to boil
for the potatoes. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel!). When
boiling add the potatoes and cook until you can easily slip a knife through, ~{15-20%mins}.
When the potato is ready, drain in a #colander{} and return to the saucepan off the heat.
Add a knob of @butter{knob} and a splash of @?milk{splash} and mash until smooth with a
#potato masher{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(halved, peeled and chopped) into small pieces.
Trim the @carrot{1}(trimmed), then quarter lengthways (no need to peel). Chop widthways
into small pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) with a #grater{}
(or use a #garlic press{}). Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on
high heat. When the oil is hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g} and cook until browned,
~{5-6%mins}. Use a #wooden spoon{} to break it up as it cooks. Once browned add the
@cornflour{20%g} and cook for ~{1-2%mins}. Transfer the beef mixture to a #plate{} and
set aside.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat.

Return the frying pan to the heat with a splash more oil if needed. Add the onion and
carrot to the pan and cook until tender ~{4-5%mins}. Add the @sliced mushrooms{150%g} and
cook until browned, ~{3-4%mins}. Add the garlic and @tomato puree{30%g} and cook for
~{1%minute}. Return the mince to the pan along with the @water{200%ml} and
@red wine stock paste{28g}. Bring to a boil and stir to dissolve the stock pot. Simmer
until the mixture has thickened, ~{1-2%mins}.

Transfer the mixture to an #ovenproof dish{} and cover with the @puff pastry sheet{3/4},
trim the edges with a sharp #knife{}. Brush the pastry with a little @?milk{little} if you
have some. Bake on the top shelf of your oven until crisp and golden brown,
~{12-15%mins}.

Heat a splash of @oil{splash} in a medium frying pan over a medium high heat. When hot,
add the @shredded Savoy cabbage{150%g} along with a splash of @?water{splash}. Season
with @salt{} and @pepper{} and cook until tender, ~{5-6%mins}.

Share the pie between your #plates{} and serve the mashed potato and cabbage on the side.
Enjoy!